cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a new architecture for sequence modeling in the NLP domain, specifically for tasks such as sentiment analysis, question classification, entailment classification, answer selection, and reading comprehension. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also focuses on the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for sequence modeling, which involves learning recurrent gating functions using recurrent networks, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper conducts experiments on tasks such as reading comprehension, which involves processing visual information, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
